records.addlTxt:
Defendant Efrain Lopez-Mendez in court with attorney John Scott Schiro.  Erin M. Karshen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case set for sentencing hearing. Sworn as Interpreter: Brenda Bartholomew. State placed negotiations on the record. Court finds the State has complied with the victim rights legislation. Statements made as to sentencing.

As to COUNT 1 as AMENDED-
Court ordered defendant to serve 60 DAYS in the House of Correction; credit for 3 days time served.

Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on probation for 6 MONTHS with the following conditions:
1) No unsupervised contact with children under the age of 16 years with the exception of the following minors:
- Y. C-F. dob 4/04/11
- A. C-F. dob 12/30/12
- D. C-F. dob 12/16/14
- J.C. dob 12/11/02
- C.C. dob 11/26/05
- B.C. 8/16/12

2) Pay all costs, fees and surcharges. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
3) Provide DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge;
4) Obtain sex offender evaluation. Court finds the sex offender evaluation completed by the defendant during the pendancy of this case satisfies this requirement;
5) Attend at least six (6) counseling sessions focused on healthy relationships and appropriate behavior on social media sites;
6) No contact with the victim;
7) Court set restitution at ZERO;

If revoked, defendant may have release for work.

Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 
Filed;
